preownedConditionTypes.conditionTypeDefinition: Item is in excellent condition, perfect working condition and has no signs of wear/usage. The original protective wrapping, if any, may be missing but the original packaging is intact.

Item is in excellent condition and has no signs of usage. The item is still in its original packaging, but packaging is open/has signs of wear. The item includes original accessories. This could include warehouse items, returns, etc.
Item shows wear from consistent use, but it remains in fair condition. The item may be marked, identified, or show other signs of previous use. The item remains usable.
A well-cared-for item that has seen limited use but remains in great condition. Item and instructions are complete and included.
A brand-new, unused functional item that has cosmetic imperfections caused during production or delivery. (Missing threads, discoloration, label malfunction, etc.)
A brand-new, unused item without original packaging.
A brand-new, unused item without original tags.
An original name brand cartridge that has been professionally cleaned, refilled with similar quality ink, and then tested to make sure you get the same print quality as the original cartridge.

product.shortDescription: Calling all health-conscious fans of air fryers. Take healthy cooking to the next level with the New Kalorik® 5 Quart Air Fryer with Ceramic Coating and Window. Say goodbye to harmful chemicals like PFOA, PTFE, and BPA because our product is free of them. Instead, we offer you a fantastic and healthy alternative – a ceramic coating that ensures your cooking experience is safe and enjoyable. With an LED touchscreen display, 10 smart presets, and adjustable time and temperature up to 400°F, you can create quick, nutritious meals with just a few taps. Ceramic coating requires less butter and oil and lets you cook at higher temperatures with the peace of mind that you are using a non-toxic and chemical-free option while enjoying the benefits of a traditional non-stick. Plenty of room in the 5-quart basket to cook 3 hamburgers or veggie patties, 6 servings of veggie florets, a whole 18-ounce fish filet, or 3 pieces of salmon. You can even fry up to 1.5 pounds of sweet potato fries. Monitor your food while cooking with the convenient viewing window and inner light – no need to disrupt the heating process. The basket and stainless-steel trivet are easy to clean for your convenience. 11.65 in depth, 10.32 lb weight.

customerReviews.reviewText: This air fryer fulfilled all the prerequisites that I was looking for.  About the right size, with a window in the front, white and within the price range that I wanted.  I love it.  It has lots of presets and is user friendly.

I finally decided to get an air fryer and found this 5qt ceramic with stainless steel tray. So far so good. Nice size and quality and quiet. Clean up is easy just soak for harder baked on food. Perfect size for 3 adults. Food taste so good cooking or reheated! I like that cooking mess is contained in the fryer and doesn't make a strong food smell throughout the house!

This air fryer has a deep basket, easy to clean, easy to handle. 
Once you have your food loaded, simply insert it fully into the fryer to activate the programmable feature, heating temperature, length of cook time. Once the desired time is chosen, press the button that looks like, “play/pause” to start the cycle. Watch the descending time along with the clear food viewing portion of the basket to see how the cooking is proceeding. The fryer has a light to illuminate the interior. Great features!
It is bigger and nicer than I thought it would be. Does more than I thought.
Works great and fast. Happy with the size. Perfect fit for my cooking needs.

So far,  I've only used it for frozen foods, and it works great. Today, I'm going to rehydrate apples with cinnamon 😋 I like the size and capacity. I understand the mode selection and toggling to select the presets, but sometimes I need to keep touching the mode to advance further, especially if I need to get to the bottom row. It's not a biggie, though. On the whole,  I like it 👌 and highly recommend it, especially with ceramic and stainless steel trivet.
